# f52e5e2893f24f2db71417eb7a72af79
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:23
msgid "Conventions"
msgstr ""

# 7bb8c3b866fa4002bbada718da03c146
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:25
msgid ""
"The conventions detailed in this chapter should be followed when "
"modifying the project documentation to maintain readability and "
"consistency."
msgstr ""

# 0f84e328263248d9bc9d1e329e826fe1
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:29
msgid "Typographic"
msgstr ""

# 904775d9d8cd47419ed1abe2bebf714a
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:43
msgid "Italic"
msgstr ""

# 6713c48318334bbc9bec7077447f8b72
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:32
msgid ""
"Used to introduce new terms. Italics used solely for emphasis should be "
"avoided. When introducing new terms, only the first use should be set in "
"italics, and its introduction should be followed with a definition or "
"description of the term."
msgstr ""

# 69eb1af2b8434a81a4eb7cee929e10cc
# 387c9d3492bf4eff927d5afe922c679b
# e6e3007a9e7d4ccd8ced41dee92cddbd
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:37
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:55
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:64
msgid "Example::"
msgstr ""

# f5bb1b7a85ab4dd0ba068565e2adb1f7
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:47
msgid "Bold"
msgstr ""

# c5fd2e20be054a149b364ac42de60531
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:46
msgid ""
"Bold typesetting is to be reserved for section, table, and glossary "
"headings and should be avoided in paragraph copy."
msgstr ""

# 436fe05f40c141c98dc0e3ca47906c2e
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:58
msgid "Monospace"
msgstr ""

# f96a5a2b63a54fa6a7a87bf251a573ea
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:50
msgid ""
"Used to indicate filesystem paths, variable names, language keywords and "
"functions, and command output. Note that in the case of variables and "
"functions, whenever possible references to their documentation should be "
"used in place of simple monospace markup."
msgstr ""

# fb93d787b8aa47cb8ada504029cf7003
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:68
msgid "Bracketed Monospace"
msgstr ""

# a0045b56e2fa41669254e0f24603d3e4
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:61
msgid ""
"Used to indicate, within command or source code examples, variables for "
"which the reader should substitute a value."
msgstr ""

# 4b4fcddb3e06498287e53840b9eb5c23
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:72
msgid "Ellipsis"
msgstr ""

# cbe229bad48c4c9a943b418e901e5d8a
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:71
msgid ""
"Used to indicate the omission of irrelevant or unimportant information. "
"May also be used to separate matter to be treated in detail elsewhere."
msgstr ""

# 2540dea31d6e43428881e10f114a74c5
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:75
msgid "Layout Styles"
msgstr ""

# 4316d9707df349c49e2bd93eedd3a476
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:78
msgid "Block Content"
msgstr ""

# 0999f4f7d32d4777a4d8a714b3d251bc
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:85
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

# 6b8ea92900314395a9cbc0e24d716baa
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:81
msgid ""
"Use of ``.. note::`` blocks should be sparing. In most rendered forms, "
"the note block will appear quite prominently and draw the readers' eyes "
"away from the surrounding copy. It is therefore advisable that the note "
"itself provide enough context and detail to be read on its own, without a"
" full reading of the surrounding copy."
msgstr ""

# d7ec7dd2130d4fbfa3a74dca8394c54a
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:96
msgid "Important Notes"
msgstr ""

# 29833ab9ac8d455ebfbca4e940fe7817
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:88
msgid ""
"The use of ``.. important::`` callout blocks should be limited only to "
"those situations in which critical information needs to be prominently "
"displayed. Suitable use would include noting that resizing a cache voiume"
" will result in |TS| resetting the cache contents to empty when the "
"service is started. This is information that may not be obvious, or safe "
"to assume, for the reader but which can significantly (and negatively) "
"impact the use and performance of |TS| in their environment. Important "
"note blocks should not be used for behavior or actions which generally do"
" not have potential negative side effects."
msgstr ""

# 51a0974ba5694112882144adee4ac579
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:100
msgid "Sidebars"
msgstr ""

# ed12c075508a4f75b7845a1384e2bc98
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:99
msgid ""
"The use of ``.. sidebar::`` blocks in |TS| documentation should be "
"avoided, and note blocks favored in their place."
msgstr ""

# 141895c0cc774ef4846ada77a9293de0
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:108
msgid "Code Samples"
msgstr ""

# 92d6939bff7341adb1cd62585d229af4
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:103
msgid ""
"Content should be set within ``.. code::`` blocks whenever a full line or"
" multiple lines of source code are being included in the documentation, "
"or when example shell or network commands are being demonstrated. Blank "
"lines may be used to separate lines of code within the block for "
"readability, and all normal indentation practices should be followed. No "
"additional markup should be used within the content block."
msgstr ""

# 3174d6b59b2c46e2ad14f974a83faebf
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:114
msgid "Definition Lists"
msgstr ""

# 7e38bf9a4272415cacd9e78c77da91de
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:111
msgid ""
"Definition lists may be used in multiple ways, not just for the term "
"listings in the glossary section. They may be used to provide individual "
"detailed treatment for a list of function or command arguments or where "
"any series of terms need to be explained outside of the formal glossary."
msgstr ""

# 1a9d2ee6fdb44dd495c9d2bea0fa884d
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:120
msgid "Ordered Lists"
msgstr ""

# 29db9303af464d72b0e953a5d73729ca
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:117
msgid ""
"Explicityly numbered ordered lists should be avoided. |RST| provides two "
"methods of marking up ordered, numbered lists, and the automatic "
"numbering form should be used in all cases where surrounding paragraphs "
"do not need to reference individual list entries."
msgstr ""

# 8f99c1236c0c4fffb2f1ea6f117232bd
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:123
msgid "Tables"
msgstr ""

# ff4d2bfebe6e461aa8256f6be55e2501
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:125
msgid ""
"Tabular content may be used in any situation where a selection of items, "
"terms, options, formats, etc. are being compared or where a grouping of "
"the same are being presented alongside a small number of attributes which"
" do not require detailed expositions."
msgstr ""

# 0b25b5bb9647444faf0544cf3f22b840
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:130
msgid ""
"The |TS| project documentation supplies a custom styling override which "
"causes cell contents to wrap within wide tables whenever possible in "
"cases where it is necessary to prevent the content from overflowing into "
"the margin. If, however, the cell content cannot be wrapped because there"
" are no breaking spaces present (for example, a long variable name "
"containing only letters, periods, underscores, dashes, and so no, but no "
"whitespace), the table may still require overflowing into the page "
"margin. Whenever possible, please try to avoid the use of tables when "
"presenting information that will lead to this, as it greatly hampers "
"readibility on smaller screens, especially tablets and mobile devices. "
"Alternatives such as a definition list may be better suited to the "
"content."
msgstr ""

# b6348bdc732e414c80e3a6703a1708f3
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:141
msgid ""
"Tables may be marked up using any of the |RST| styles, though it is "
"generally easiest to maintain those using the *simple* table markup "
"style."
msgstr ""

# 1974466cf26c4d1ca19a2692954fd97a
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:145
msgid "Structural"
msgstr ""

# 074bc8f45b2746fc85c0333ea9e6e937
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:148
msgid "Common Definitions"
msgstr ""

# 456de22bbe6f473983b6acfe7a5288c9
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:150
msgid ""
"The |TS| project documentation maintains a common definitions, "
"abbreviations, and shortcut listing in the file ``doc/common.defs``. This"
" file should be included by all |RST| source files after the standard "
"project copyright notice."
msgstr ""

# 8982507b39824317bbcdc3573c1ea967
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:154
msgid ""
"The file should always be included using a relative path from the current"
" file's location. Any commonly or repeatedly used abbreviations, "
"especialy those of product, company, or person names, should be added to "
"the definitions file as useful to avoid repetitive typing and ensure "
"accurate spellings or legal usage."
msgstr ""

# 9fb56d7300a5465997edb8cf33bed2c8
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:160
msgid "Tables of Content"
msgstr ""

# db9d1643dbb34225958a2bacf7daa831
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:162
msgid ""
"Any chapters of non-trivial scope should begin with a table of contents "
"on the chapter index. The ``:depth:`` option for the table of contents "
"may be set to a value appropriate to the amount of content in the chapter"
" sections. A depth of ``2`` will generally provide a balance between "
"usefully describing the contents of the chapter without overwhelming a "
"reader scanning for topics relevant to their needs or interests."
msgstr ""

# 0831871b6a7746a3a629340cfbd0bf30
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:170
msgid "Sections and Headings"
msgstr ""

# 5aac1e2558ea4fa68c656c9c00bc5dd7
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:172
msgid ""
"Each chapter section should be located in a separate |RST| file. Each "
"file should contain the standard project copyright notice first, followed"
" by a unique reference marker for the section."
msgstr ""

# 5716c457dce348f88b9cb00f2fe9b617
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:176
msgid ""
"While |RST| itself does not define a fixed ordering of section markers, "
"|TS| documentation source files should use the same set of single line "
"section markings, proceeding through the section levels without skipping."
" For consistency, the following section line markers should be used in "
"order::"
msgstr ""

# 7abc67b4a2e8496bb6d67b63fd18d9d5
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:193
msgid ""
"Any section file which reaches or has need to exceed the fourth level "
"style of section line markings is an excellent candidate for breaking "
"into several smaller, and ideally more focused, |RST| source files and "
"referenced by an index with its own table of contents."
msgstr ""

# 2e0d227428644131b6c4262cb677b38f
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:199
msgid "Footnotes and Endnotes"
msgstr ""

# 8b98dcb47b9f42ce8532c2b07ffb2d06
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:201
msgid ""
"Both footnotes and endnotes should be avoided. The |TS| documentation is "
"intended primarily for online viewing and the positioning of footnotes in"
" the rendered output is not always intuitive. In cases where a footnote "
"might have been appropriate in print-oriented material for referencing an"
" external resource, that reference is more ideally integrated as a "
"standard |RST| reference."
msgstr ""

# 4b90cc98839949158980621fe332ad04
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:208
msgid ""
"For more descriptive content that might have been included as a footnote,"
" it is less disruptive and more useful to choose between reformullating "
"the text to simply include the additional wording, or consider the use of"
" an inline note block."
msgstr ""

# 43197aa8d7fe48ab96a6cb6da5a4bf21
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/conventions.en.rst:214
msgid "Grammatical"
msgstr ""

